  "subject": "Cache rbac mappings from keycloak",
  "commit_message": "Cache rbac mappings from keycloak\n\n- replace current implementation that issues\n  one request to keycloak per northbound request\n- cache rbac permissions by jwt id in memory\n- this is done by replacing the authorized: true/false\n  request to keycloak with a request to fetch all permissions\n  for the user and then caching that for the authorized session\n- expire the cached auth once the ttl (time to live) of the token\n  expires\n- fix GHA pipeline\n- relying on spring security for this was evaluated, but not possible\n  with webflux and under the constraint that all RBAC related config\n  shall be solely coming from keycloak\n\nIssue-ID: PORTALNG-170\nChange-Id: I8a7f5cb9b06d5d53114bcfa6bd7c7f9c5e64263d\nSigned-off-by: Fiete Ostkamp <fiete.ostkamp@telekom.de>\n",
